# Tailwind CSS Styling Conventions

## Tailwind is the only styling method

Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively. Do not use CSS modules, styled-components, or inline `style` props.

## Color palette

Use the **slate** scale as the base:

| Use | Class |
|-----|-------|
| Page background | `bg-slate-50` |
| Primary text | `text-slate-900` |
| Dark sections (navbar, buttons) | `bg-slate-900` |
| Cards / panels | `bg-slate-100` |
| Borders | `border-slate-400` |
| Muted text | `text-slate-500` |

## Layout

Full-height page layout with a sticky header and scrollable body:

```jsx
// Root wrapper
<div className="bg-slate-50 h-screen text-slate-900 flex flex-col overflow-hidden">
  <Navbar />
  <main className="flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-auto">
    <Outlet />
  </main>
</div>
```

Centering and constrained-width content:

```jsx
<div className="flex justify-center mt-8">
  <div className="w-[90%] md:w-[60%]"> ... </div>
</div>
```

## Reusable class strings

Store repeated class strings in a `const` at the top of the component:

```jsx
// ✅ GOOD
const buttonClassName = "border-1 bg-slate-900 text-white border-slate-400 rounded-lg px-4 py-1 hover:bg-white hover:text-slate-900 hover:cursor-pointer transition-all duration-600";

<button className={buttonClassName}>Submit</button>
<button className={buttonClassName}>Cancel</button>
```

## Interactive states

```
hover:cursor-pointer    — clickable non-button elements
hover:underline         — link-like text
hover:bg-*              — background change on hover
hover:scale-110         — subtle scale on hover
transition-all duration-300  — smooth transitions
```

## Dynamic classes

Use template literals for conditional classes:

```jsx
<div className={`flex flex-col ${isFull ? 'mb-3' : ''}`}>
```
